Conditionals
If statments evaluate an expression
If the expression returns true, the code in the block after will be exectuted, otherwise the block of code will get skipped.
It will then continue if there are other statements such as if else or else statements.
In the case of an else statement if the expression returns false then the code block after the else statement will be executed.
Return Statements
Terminates a method before you reach the end
Recusive Functions
Functions that call on themselves
